	Straight Spears    
	 New York, Oct. 10 (Reuters): Pop star Britney Spears plans to set the record straight about her personal and professional woes in a documentary to be aired shortly before the release of her new album Circus in December.      
	 the 90-minute film, Britney: For the Record, Spears talks about her high-profile meltdown, which included stints in rehab and psychiatric hospital units, an ugly divorce, losing custody of her two sons and shaving her head.      
	I sit there and Ill look back and Im like: Im a smart person. What the hell was I thinking? the 26-year-old singer says in the documentary shot by filmmaker Phil Griffin over three-months.      
	So much has gone on over the last couple of years and theres a lot that people dont know about me that I want them to know, Spears said in a statement.                                                                                                                                                                           
